<item>
            <title>[QPIDJMS-237] Connection doesn&apos;t always shutdown its internal threads on connection loss</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-237</link>
                <project id="12314524" key="QPIDJMS">Qpid JMS</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the connection receives a connection level error it closes down its internal resources but doesn&apos;t ensure that its internal task runner thread is shutdown which can lead a build up of connection threads if external error handler don&apos;t immediately close the connection.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
